@cebe I've checked, actually it already allows using `Expression` for order by.
following test is passed successfully

```
$query->orderBy(new Expression('CASE WHEN x = y THEN 0 ELSE 1 END'));
$this->assertEquals(['CASE WHEN x = y THEN 0 ELSE 1 END' => SORT_ASC], $query->orderBy);
```

Expressions are processing here https://github.com/yiisoft/yii2/blob/master/framework/db/QueryBuilder.php#L801

So I guess there is no need to change anything.

The only thing that I can add test above to test case because there is no such test currently
